Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(contacts): phone + CSV/vCard contact import +
 work-email filter

Extend the existing email_contacts pipeline with phone import and a
work-email filter. CSV upload already shipped; this adds:

- Shared upsert core (lib/email/upsert-contacts.ts) every path funnels
  through; fixes the 2026-06-13 audit MEDIUM (re-upload nulled a name).
- Work-email filter (partitionContacts) applied to Google AND CSV.
- Google sign-in import: read-only OAuth (no SDK, token never stored) +
  pure People->ContactRow mapper + start/callback routes (CSRF state).
- Android QR: signed import token (HMAC on SDG_COOKIE_SECRET, 10-min TTL)
  -> desktop QR -> /m/contacts/[token] + Contact Picker API (feature
  detected, iPhone fallback) -> token-authed phone route (service-role).
- vCard (.vcf) parser wired into the upload route + file picker.
- Extracted makeSupabaseAudienceStore (explicit user_id scoping) and
  reused it in /sync.

tsc 0, eslint clean, next build compiles + typechecks, 3055 tests pass.
.env.example documents GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID/SECRET (sensitive scope ->
needs People API enable + OAuth verification).

